newsitem.title: FRANCE: No deliveries seen on MATIF September wheat.
newsitem.headline: No deliveries seen on MATIF September wheat.

text.p: The first trading month of MATIF wheat futures, September 1996, goes off the board tonight and signs are there will be no deliveries, traders said.
Two lots traded in September on Wednesday and although positions have yet to be tallied these are seen cancelling the two positions left open in the market on Tuesday.
MATIF launched wheat on July 5 but the late timing of the launch discouraged trade on the first expiry month, traders said. Legal problems had delayed by the launch by some months.
Traders said most September cash had been covered, pushing trade interest into November with open interest of 257 lots.
